        public Disk(int spawn,
            Vector coord,
            Vector vec,
            Vector acc,
            double finalRadius,
            double radiusChange,
            boolean circularMotion,
            double degree,
            double degreeChange,
            double towardsCenter,
            javafx.scene.shape.Circle circularPath,
            Delay delay,
            Delay lifeSpan,
            boolean safe,
            boolean redirect)
        this is the constructor for the disk class
        Parameters:
        spawn - the frame the circle spawns on the screen
        coord - its coordinates
        vec - its vector
        acc - its acceleration
        finalRadius - the radius it should finish off with
        radiusChange - changes the radius of the circle
        circularMotion - this will say if its going to move in a circle
        degree - the degree on the circular path it will be on
        degreeChange - change the degree each frame by this amount
        towardsCenter - change the radius of the circular path
        circularPath - this is the circular path, it will travel on the parameter of the circular
        delay - this is the amount of frames the warning will last before the real circle spawns
        lifeSpan - the amount of frames the circle will last on the screen
        safe - if this is a safe zone
        redirect - if the circle will be redirected
